---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = 'Accessibility Statement | Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS - Manteca Dentist';
const description = 'Accessibility statement for Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS. Our commitment to making our website and dental practice accessible to everyone.';
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
    <p>Our commitment to accessibility for all patients and visitors</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Our Commitment to Accessibility</h2>
    <p>At the dental practice of Dr. Alan S. Lee, DDS, we are committed to ensuring that our website and dental office are accessible to everyone, including individuals with disabilities. We strive to comply with the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA) and the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards.</p>

    <h2>Website Accessibility</h2>
    <p>We are continuously working to improve the accessibility of our website to ensure it is usable by all visitors. Our efforts include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Keyboard navigation:</strong> Our website is designed to be navigable using keyboard controls</li>
      <li><strong>Alt text:</strong> We provide alternative text for all meaningful images</li>
      <li><strong>Color contrast:</strong> We maintain sufficient color contrast for readability</li>
      <li><strong>Heading structure:</strong> We use proper heading hierarchy for screen reader navigation</li>
      <li><strong>Form labels:</strong> All form fields are properly labeled for assistive technology</li>
      <li><strong>Responsive design:</strong> Our website is designed to work on all device sizes</li>
      <li><strong>Clear language:</strong> We use clear and simple language throughout our website</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Office Accessibility</h2>
    <p>Our dental office is designed to be accessible to patients with disabilities:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Wheelchair-accessible entrance and treatment areas</li>
      <li>Accessible restroom facilities</li>
      <li>Accommodations for patients with mobility challenges</li>
      <li>Assistance available for patients who need help navigating our office</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Ongoing Efforts</h2>
    <p>We regularly review and test our website for accessibility. We are committed to making ongoing improvements to ensure our digital presence is inclusive and accessible. We follow the WCAG 2.1 Level AA guidelines as our standard and work to exceed them whenever possible.</p>

    <h2>Third-Party Content</h2>
    <p>While we strive to ensure all content on our website is accessible, some third-party content (such as embedded forms and maps) may not fully conform to our accessibility standards. We work with our third-party providers to encourage accessibility improvements and are committed to finding accessible alternatives when needed.</p>

    <h2>Feedback &amp; Assistance</h2>
    <p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website and dental office. If you encounter any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please let us know:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+12092392990">(209) 239-2990</a></li>
      <li><strong>In person:</strong> 715 N Main St, Manteca, CA 95336</li>
      <li><strong>Online:</strong> <a href="/contact-the-office/">Contact us through our website</a></li>
    </ul>
    <p>We will make every reasonable effort to provide accessible alternatives and address any accessibility concerns promptly.</p>

    <h2>Accessibility Standards</h2>
    <p>We aim to conform to the following accessibility standards:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA:</strong> Web Content Accessibility Guidelines developed by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C)</li>
      <li><strong>ADA:</strong> Americans with Disabilities Act requirements for public accommodations</li>
      <li><strong>Section 508:</strong> Federal accessibility standards for electronic and information technology</li>
      <li><strong>California ADA:</strong> California-specific accessibility requirements</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Assistive Technology Compatibility</h2>
    <p>Our website is designed to be compatible with commonly used assistive technologies, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Screen readers (JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver)</li>
      <li>Screen magnification software</li>
      <li>Voice recognition software</li>
      <li>Alternative keyboard and pointing devices</li>
    </ul>

    <p>This accessibility statement was last reviewed and updated in January 2024.</p>
  </section>
</Layout>